<title>BELGIUM: EU in last-ditch bid for slice of Korean market.</title>
<headline>EU in last-ditch bid for slice of Korean market.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The European Union is making a last-ditch attempt to prise open access to South Korea's lucrative $8 billion-a-year telecommunications market, the European Commission said on Monday.</p>
<p>A statement said EU Trade Commissioner Sir Leon Brittan would meet South Korean Foreign Minister Gou Ro Myung in Luxembourg on October 28 to try to settle a long-running dispute over market access.</p>
<p>It said Korean legislation and other barriers were denying European companies potential business worth hundreds of millions of dollars.</p>
<p>Two years of talks had failed to resolve differences, the statement said, and this was a &quot;last-ditcH attempt&quot; to settle the matter.</p>
<p>Commission sources have said the EU would consider escalating the dispute at the World Trade Organisation if it was not satisfied with the outcome.</p>
</text>
